# 📘 CORD-19 Metadata Analysis & Streamlit App

## 🔹 Overview
This project explores the **CORD-19 research dataset** (metadata.csv) to practice basic **data analysis**, **visualization**, and building a simple **Streamlit application**.  

You’ll learn how to:
- Load and clean a real-world dataset  
- Explore COVID-19 research trends  
- Visualize insights with charts and word clouds  
- Build an interactive Streamlit dashboard  

---

## 📊 Dataset
We use **metadata.csv** from the [CORD-19 dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/allen-institute-for-ai/CORD-19-research-challenge).  

The metadata file contains:
- Paper titles and abstracts  
- Publication dates  
- Authors and journals  
- Source information  

⚠️ The full dataset is very large — this project uses only `metadata.csv`.

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Requirements
- Python **3.7+**  
- [pandas](https://pandas.pydata.org/) → data manipulation  
- [matplotlib](https://matplotlib.org/) & [seaborn](https://seaborn.pydata.org/) → visualization  
- [wordcloud](https://github.com/amueller/word_cloud) → text visualization  
- [streamlit](https://streamlit.io/) → interactive web app  

### Install dependencies
```bash
pip install pandas matplotlib seaborn wordcloud streamlit
